Introduction
This is the most recent version of the National Statistical API (v3.5, May 2025). It is a half-version upgrade and is fully backward-compatible with v3.0 (May 2024).

For applications built between May 2022 and April 2024, please refer to the API v2 documentation. For applications built between March 2018 and April 2022, please refer to the API v1 documentation. API v1 was taken offline on December 31, 2024.

  All National Statistical subscriptions include hourly API calls. NatStat offers a range of monthly and annual subscription packages for one or multiple data services, with recurring and non-recurring payment options to fit your budget and needs. Click here to find out more.

  NatStat API v3.5 contains 29 data endpoints. Click here to view the detailed endpoint reference.

The National Statistical API is a REST-ful data service offering real-time and historical data for 29 national, international and collegiate competition levels of basketball, baseball, hockey, American football and soccer. It is owned and operated by National Statistical, which has been offering sports data services since 2007.

This is a paid service limited to National Statistical customers who have purchased subscriptions, and is limited to data associated with active subscriptions.

The design of our databases and delivery systems is ©2007-2025 National Statistical. Usage of this system and provided services grants a non-exclusive commercial license for any and all data retrieved via our websites and API. We are not responsible for any data or financial loss/damages that arise from use of our systems; please refer to our legal disclaimer for more information on liability, warranties and exceptions/exclusions. Also please refer to our policies on API abuse, detailed below in this document.

