curl_close($ch);
print_r(json_decode($data));
Python
import requests
url = "https://api3.natst.at/xxxx-xxxxxx/..."
print(requests.get(url).json())
Parameters
API Key
Each valid request requires the inclusion of a valid API key as a query parameter. A key contains 11 characters: four alphanumeric characters, a dash, then six alphanumeric characters. Your account's current API key can be found on the National Statistical account page (requires login, located underneath the list of active subscriptions. (For new accounts, please note that it may take a few minutes to generate an initial API key.)

https://api3.natst.at/xxxx-xxxxxx/...

If no key is specified, an AUTHORIZE_FAILED error will be returned. If an invalid key is specified, a UNAUTHORIZED error will be returned.

