Basic Response
Success
Responses in JSON and XML include a success node. If 1 is returned, the passed URI query is valid, and the database has been successfully queried. If 0 is returned, more information on the reason why the request failed will be included in the error or meta node.

[success] => 1

Errors
Below are common errors returned by the API. These will be contained in the error node.

UNDER_MAINTENANCE	The API is undergoing maintenance or temporary downtime. In the case of scheduled maintenance, the meta block will include details on when the API will be active again.
AUTHORIZE_FAILED	The key is incorrect, invalid, or expired. Please refer to your account page (requires login) to check the API key.
NO_ENDPOINT	A valid endpoint has not been specified. Please refer to the list of endpoints for guidance.
PARAMETER_MISSING	A valid sport or level path parameter has not been specified. Please refer to the list of acceptable values.
CONCURRENCY	The API key is attempting more than four queries per second, which is not permitted. This can be circumvented by subscribing to API+, which removes IP and concurrency restrictions.
OUT_OF_RANGE	This message occurs when the API key is not valid for the sport requested (e.g. the API key is owned by a user with a valid NBA subscription, and the MBB endpoint is called).
OUT_OF_CALLS	The API key has exceeded its rate limit. Please refer to information on rate limits.
TOO_MANY_IPBLOCKS	The key has accessed the API from too many different IP blocks (X.X.-.-) within a 24-hour period. This can be circumvented by subscribing to API+, which removes IP and concurrency restrictions.
APIPLUS_ONLY	You've attempted to access a premium service or closed beta that is only available to API+ subscribers. This can be remedied by subscribing to API+.
BLOCKED	The API key has been temporarily suspended or permanently revoked, and you have been sent an email detailing why.
User Node
The user node is stamped with the authorized National Statistical account username attached to the API key, the sport levels the account is authorized to access via the API. This node also contains data on rate limits.

All National Statistical API-enabled accounts are rate limited. All rate limits reset at the top of each hour. The user node includes information on the API key's current rate limitation status. Please review our three-strike policies on API abuse.

