API Key Reset
If you have found that your API key (or code containing the key) has been compromised or forgotten, a new key can be easily generated.

To reset your API key, navigate to Analysis Tools > NatStat API > Query Builder within a subsite that you have access to.

Multiple IP Policy
Account sharing is strictly prohibited, and controlling data traffic is paramount to maintaining low customer prices for you. Each API key is allowed access from up to four IP blocks (X.X.-.-) within any 24 hour period, which are listed in the meta node as ip-last24. Accessing the NatStat API from more than six IP blocks within 24 hours will result in an automatic 24-hour suspension of service.

