Path Parameters
apikey  required    A valid API key in xxxx-xxxxxx format. This must be the first path parameter. Example: https://api3.natst.at/xxxx-xxxxxx/...
endpoint  required    The API endpoint to query. This must be the second path parameter. Example: https://api3.natst.at/xxxx-xxxxxx/datastatus/...
service required    One of 30 NatStat data services to query. A full list can be found in the documentation. This must be the third path parameter. Example: https://api3.natst.at/xxxx-xxxxxx/datastatus/nhl/...
Range Parameters
Range parameters are optional comma-separated values placed after the API key, endpoint and service code in the URI. Values may be used in combination to further refine a search.

dataformat  optional    Controls the data format by which query results are returned. Acceptable values are xml, json or php. The default value is json. Example: https://api3.natst.at/xxxx-xxxxxx/datastatus/nba/xml
season  optional    A valid season code (the year when a particular season completes) in YYYY format. A list of available values can be retrieved from the /seasons endpoint. Example: https://api3.natst.at/xxxx-xxxxxx/datastatus/nba/2025
Pagination Parameter
Please note that when pagination is used with a query without a range parameter, an underscore must be placed in the fourth slash position so that the URI remains valid.

offset  optional    A fifth (optional) path parameter is a paginated "offset" number for recordsets exceeding 100. The default is 0, the beginning of the recordset. Example: https://api3.natst.at/xxxx-xxxxxx/datastatus/nba/_/100
 

